Task 3: Directory and File Discovery with ffuf
Step 3.1: Basic Directory Fuzzing
Perform basic directory discovery:

ffuf -w ~/wordlists/common.txt \
     -u http://localhost/DVWA/FUZZ \
     -o ffuf_directories.json \
     -of json \
     -t 50 \
     -mc 200,301,302,403 \
     -c
Parameters explained:

-w: Wordlist to use
-u: Target URL with FUZZ keyword
-o: Output file
-of: Output format
-t: Number of threads
-mc: Match HTTP status codes
-c: Colorized output
Step 3.2: File Extension Fuzzing
Create a script for file discovery with multiple extensions:

#!/bin/bash
# File: file_discovery.sh

TARGET="http://localhost/DVWA"
WORDLIST="$HOME/wordlists/common.txt"
EXTENSIONS="php,txt,html,js,css,xml,json,bak,old,conf"

echo "Starting file extension fuzzing..."

ffuf -w $WORDLIST \
     -u $TARGET/FUZZ \
     -e $EXTENSIONS \
     -o ffuf_files.json \
     -of json \
     -t 50 \
     -mc 200,301,302,403 \
     -c

echo "Results saved to ffuf_files.json"
Execute the script:

chmod +x file_discovery.sh
./file_discovery.sh
